                <h1>Discover Verizon's Evolution: From 2000 to 5G Leader</h1>
                <p>Verizon's history dates back to 2000 when it emerged from the merger of Bell Atlantic and GTE. Initially focused on regional telecommunications, it quickly expanded into wireless services, becoming one of the largest providers in the U.S. Known for innovation, Verizon has invested heavily in 5G and fiber-optic technologies, shaping the modern communication landscape.</p>
